Searchlight Capital Partners Closes Second Fund at $1.9 Billion






December 17, 2015 06:26 PM Eastern Standard Time



NEW YORK--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Searchlight Capital Partners, L.P. (“Searchlight”), today announced the 
      final close of Searchlight Capital II, L.P. (“the Fund”) with total 
      committed capital of over $1.9 billion.
    

      Commenting on the Fund closing, Erol Uzumeri, a Founding Partner of 
      Searchlight, said: “We are very grateful for the support of our existing 
      and new investors from around the globe. We remain committed to creating 
      value within our partner companies by providing thoughtful strategic 
      direction and flexible capital. Our transatlantic platform, fully 
      integrated team, and differentiated investment mandate allow Searchlight 
      to capitalize on a wide range of global opportunities across multiple 
      industries.”
    

      Latham & Watkins LLP served as legal counsel to the Fund and Park Hill 
      Group served as placement agent.
    

About Searchlight Capital Partners, L.P.


      Searchlight is a global private investment firm with offices in New 
      York, London and Toronto.
    

      Searchlight invests in businesses where its long term capital and 
      strategic support accelerate value creation for all stakeholders. For 
      more information, please visit www.searchlightcap.com.
    




